From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000026 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:05:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] usb: phy: generic: get the optional vbus supply with the
 optional getter

usb_phy_generic asks for its vbus supply (a charging current sink used
only in OTG b-peripheral mode) with devm_regulator_get_exclusive() and
then maps -ENODEV to "no vbus". The regulator core refuses to hand out
dummy supplies for exclusive requests, warning

  usb_phy_generic hsusb1-phy: dummy supplies not allowed for exclusive requests (id=vbus)

on every boot of any board that simply has no vbus supply (e.g. the
Nexus Q host-only hsusb1 PHY). Use devm_regulator_get_optional(): it
returns -ENODEV silently for an absent supply, which the existing
NULL-mapping already handles, and still returns a real, exclusively
usable regulator when one is wired in the DT.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
--- a/drivers/usb/phy/phy-generic.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/phy/phy-generic.c
@@ -256,7 +256,15 @@
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, PTR_ERR(nop->vcc),
 				     "could not get vcc regulator\n");
 
-	nop->vbus_draw = devm_regulator_get_exclusive(dev, "vbus");
+	/*
+	 * vbus is genuinely optional (a charging current sink used only in
+	 * OTG b-peripheral mode). The exclusive getter made the regulator
+	 * core warn "dummy supplies not allowed for exclusive requests
+	 * (id=vbus)" on every boot of a board without a vbus supply; the
+	 * optional getter returns -ENODEV silently, which the existing
+	 * NULL-mapping below already handles.
+	 */
+	nop->vbus_draw = devm_regulator_get_optional(dev, "vbus");
 	if (PTR_ERR(nop->vbus_draw) == -ENODEV)
 		nop->vbus_draw = NULL;
 	if (IS_ERR(nop->vbus_draw))
